Storage Architecture
Direct-attached storage DAS
	ATA -Advanced Technology Attachment
	IDE -Integrated Drive Electronics
	SCSI 
	Fibre Channel
	SAS -Serial Attached SCSI
	SATA -Serial ATA
	eSATA -external SATA
	USB3 -Extensible Host Controller Interface
	Firewire

Storage area networks SAN
	iFCP -Fibre Channel extension IP
	FCoE -Fibre Channel over Ethernet
	iSCSI -Internet SCSI
	RDMA-iSER -Remote Directly Memory Access
	SRP -SCSI RDMA Protocol
	ATAoE -ATA over Ethernet

Network-attached storage NAS
	NFS -Network File System
	SMB/CIFS -Server Message Block/Common Internet File System
	
Storage services:
LVM -Logical volume management

Storage features:
Data integrity
	DIF -Data integrity field 
		8byte trailer: 2bytes CRC(Cyclic redundancy check), 2bytes Application tag, 4bytes Reference tag

Support for solid-state disks(SSDs)

File system:
EXT3/4 -Extended file system
ZFS
BTRFS -Butter FS

Distribute file system:
Lustre
Ceph
GlusterFS -General Parallel File System

CentOS -Community Enterprise Operating System